# Workers' District around Kalev's smithy. Building footprints and
# street spacing are doubled while doors, props, and character-scale details stay readable.
# The south-west Karja/Vaike-Karja edge is an interior district seam to the
# Southern Quarter; the exterior Karja Gate and south wall live on south_quarter.
rrmap 1
map lower_town_slice loc.lower_town_slice 152 128 grass scope=production active=true palette=clean_painted seed=42042 cell_size=32
# 1343 material mix (docs/HISTORICAL_AUDIT.md): church, monastery, and rich
# merchant houses in local limestone under ceramic tile; middle burgher houses
# plastered or plank-clad under wooden shingle; poorer lanes and the suburbs
# outside the wall in horizontal log under reed/straw thatch; brick stays a
# single rare accent (Reval built limestone, not brick Gothic).
